"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The DBSCAN implementation in scikit-learn expects the input data to be either a feature array or a distance matrix if the metric is set to 'precomputed'. In the provided code, the custom distance function `get_point_distance` is used directly as the metric, which is not supported by DBSCAN. The metric parameter should be a string or a callable that is one of the options allowed by `sklearn.metrics.pairwise_distances`.\",\n  \"patch\": \"35c35\\n< clustering = DBSCAN(metric=get_point_distance).fit(\\n---\\n> clustering = DBSCAN(metric='precomputed').fit(\\n36a37\\n> distance_matrix = euclidean_distances(np.array([point.to_list() for point in points]))\\n37c38\\n<     np.array([point.to_list() for point in points])\\n---\\n>     distance_matrix\\n\"\n}"